WEBVTT

00:13.013 --> 00:14.681
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:14.715 --> 00:16.617
I CAN'T TAKE THIS.
NOT NOW.

00:16.650 --> 00:19.019
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE GIRL
BEGGING ME FOR 60 POUNDS?

00:19.052 --> 00:21.154
SHE HAS COMPETITION
MUSCLING IN.

00:21.188 --> 00:22.589
I'M EXPOSED ON THIS ONE.

00:22.623 --> 00:26.260
I OWE NOW, SO IT'S
KIND OF BOTH OUR PROBLEM.

00:26.293 --> 00:29.363
THE S. E. C. KNOWS
YOUR FUND IS A PONZI SCHEME.

00:29.396 --> 00:30.964
THEY'RE GONNA
COME AFTER YOU.

00:30.998 --> 00:31.865
SO WE'RE COOKING THE BOOKS?

00:31.899 --> 00:33.800
Klein was
the cash guy.

00:33.834 --> 00:35.669
We need the money.
I will get it.

00:35.702 --> 00:37.838
SHANE'S NOT INVOLVED.

00:37.871 --> 00:39.139
WELL, HE'S ASKED
ABOUT POUNCY HOUSE.

00:39.173 --> 00:40.941
IT'S MY OLDER SON, SILAS.

00:40.974 --> 00:42.476
WHAT'S HIS CONNECTION
WITH THEM?

00:42.509 --> 00:45.646
HE'S JUST SLEEPING
WITH SOME GIRL, EMMA.
SHE'S THE BOSS.

00:45.679 --> 00:48.949
SHANE JUST BLINDLY JUST FOLLOWS
HIS OLDER BROTHER.

00:48.982 --> 00:50.184
YOU ASKING FOR HELP?

00:51.318 --> 00:54.588
A CALL COMES IN,
ALEX TAKES A CODE,

00:54.621 --> 00:55.956
THE CODE GOES INTO THE BRAIN,
WHERE IT BECOMES A SALE.

00:55.989 --> 00:57.624
YOU HAVE THE BETTER POT.

00:57.658 --> 01:00.827
BUT YOU HAVE THE BETTER
DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM.

01:00.861 --> 01:01.929
FINE.
FINE.

01:01.962 --> 01:03.597
FINE.

01:03.630 --> 01:04.598
ONE BUST.

01:04.631 --> 01:07.601
CALL OFF THE CAVALRY.
I'VE SOLVED OUR PROBLEM.

01:07.634 --> 01:09.770
NANCY: <i>Hi, it's Nancy.</i>
<i>Leave your message.</i>

01:09.803 --> 01:10.904
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO KNOW...

01:10.938 --> 01:12.172
I SOLVED OUR PROBLEM.

01:12.206 --> 01:15.409
‐‐ Captions by VITAC ‐‐
www.vitac.com

01:29.456 --> 01:30.757
NO.

01:30.791 --> 01:32.893
IT'S ALREADY DONE.
I'VE AGREED TO IT.

01:32.926 --> 01:36.463
I'M RUNNING IT PAST YOU
AS A COURTESY.

01:36.496 --> 01:37.998
I GAVE HER MY WORD.

01:38.031 --> 01:39.066
AND THE WORD IS "NO."

01:39.099 --> 01:40.400
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOUR MOM?

01:40.434 --> 01:42.302
MERGING IS THE ONLY WAY
TO GO.

01:42.336 --> 01:44.838
WITH OUR SUPPLY LINES AND ‐‐
AND HER CUSTOMER BASE ‐‐

01:44.872 --> 01:46.573
YOU MEAN
OUR CUSTOMER BASE.

01:46.607 --> 01:49.142
FOOTNOTE, THEY WERE MY CUSTOMERS
BEFORE YOU STOLE THEM.

01:49.176 --> 01:52.679
FOOTNOTE, THEY'RE ABOUT TO BE
MY CUSTOMERS AGAIN.

01:52.713 --> 01:53.981
DEAL'S OFF.

01:54.014 --> 01:56.383
YOUR MOM CLEARLY HAS
THE CONTROLLING INTEREST HERE

01:56.416 --> 01:57.317
AND SHE'S A BITCH.

01:57.351 --> 01:59.786
WHEN I NEED TO BE.
YOU WANT TO TRY ME?

01:59.820 --> 02:01.955
[ SCOFFS ]

02:01.989 --> 02:03.924
EMMA!

02:03.957 --> 02:05.325
LET HER GO.

02:05.359 --> 02:06.994
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

02:07.027 --> 02:09.396
I THOUGHT I MADE THIS
PRETTY CLEAR.

02:09.429 --> 02:11.932
I'M NOT
YOUR EMPLOYEE ANYMORE.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.800
AND WHEN I DECIDE
THAT SOMETHING'S RIGHT FOR US,

02:13.834 --> 02:14.935
I EXPECT YOU
TO BACK ME UP.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.970
WHERE IS ALL THIS MACHO BULLSHIT
COMING FROM?

02:17.004 --> 02:18.071
YOU USED TO BE SO SWEET.

02:18.105 --> 02:19.840
YOU MEAN "STUPID."

02:19.873 --> 02:22.409
THAT IS NOT AT ALL
WHAT I MEANT.

02:22.442 --> 02:23.944
EVERY TIME YOU TELL ME
TO DO SOMETHING,

02:23.977 --> 02:26.013
YOU GET THIS CONDESCENDING LOOK
ON YOUR FACE.

02:26.046 --> 02:28.849
YOUR MOUTH STARTS CONFIGURING
INTO THIS LITTLE SMIRK.

02:28.882 --> 02:31.151
YOU MEAN "CONTORTING."

02:32.386 --> 02:33.687
JOKE. SORRY.

02:33.720 --> 02:35.789
THIS IS A RIDICULOUS
CONVERSATION.

02:35.822 --> 02:37.057
YOU'RE A VERY BRIGHT KID.

02:37.090 --> 02:39.593
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

02:39.626 --> 02:41.962
I'M A GROWN MAN.

02:41.995 --> 02:44.631
OKAY. NO.

02:44.665 --> 02:45.966
I'M YOUR MOTHER!

02:45.999 --> 02:48.068
TO ME, YOU'RE A KID ‐‐
ALWAYS WILL BE. SORRY.

02:48.101 --> 02:49.269
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW,

02:49.303 --> 02:51.104
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING TO DO
WITH THAT GIRL.

02:51.138 --> 02:53.640
NEITHER DO YOU,
TRUST ME.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.609
I GOT TO GO.

02:59.947 --> 03:01.381
IT'S THE SMART MOVE.

03:01.415 --> 03:04.985
COMPANIES MERGE, AND THEN
THEY DESTROY THE COMPETITION.

03:05.018 --> 03:06.286
BIGGER IS BETTER.

03:06.320 --> 03:08.822
SHE WON'T LISTEN
TO ANYBODY ELSE.

03:08.856 --> 03:10.891
TOTAL FUCKING
CONTROL FREAK.

03:10.924 --> 03:12.125
SHE WON'T SAY IT
TO MY FACE,

03:12.159 --> 03:13.994
BUT SHE THINKS BECAUSE LARS
IS A FUCKING IDIOT

03:14.027 --> 03:14.995
THAT I MUST BE, TOO.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.897
WHO'S LARS?

03:16.930 --> 03:18.298
MY DAD.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.400
NO, HE'S NOT REALLY MY DAD.
MY REAL DAD WAS SOMEONE ELSE.

03:20.434 --> 03:24.371
HE'S MY BIOLOGICAL DAD.
[ SIGHS ]

03:24.404 --> 03:26.940
I GUESS THAT'S MY REAL DAD,
THOUGH, RIGHT? FUCK.

03:26.974 --> 03:28.809
IS HE REALLY AN IDIOT?

03:28.842 --> 03:30.844
HIS TEETH ARE BRIGHTER
THAN HE IS, YOU KNOW?

03:30.878 --> 03:34.314
EVER BEEN TO THERAPY?

03:34.348 --> 03:38.385
I ALREADY FUCKING KNOW.
IT'S ALL ABOUT MY MOM.

03:39.887 --> 03:41.455
SO COME WORK FOR ME.

03:41.488 --> 03:43.957
NO OFFENSE,

03:43.991 --> 03:46.393
BUT I'M NOT GONNA TRADE IN
ONE BOSS FOR ANOTHER.

03:46.426 --> 03:48.529
MY "LOYAL SOLDIER" DAYS
ARE OVER.

03:48.562 --> 03:49.997
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

03:50.030 --> 03:52.232
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T KNOW.

03:53.634 --> 03:55.602
I'LL FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.972
THANKS FOR THE OFFER,
THOUGH.

03:59.006 --> 04:01.742
ALWAYS ON THE TABLE...

04:01.775 --> 04:03.610
IF YOU WANT IT.

04:08.148 --> 04:10.517
I'D RATHER HAVE YOU
ON THE TABLE.

04:19.826 --> 04:21.929
Nancy:
SHANE, WHERE'S SILAS?

04:21.962 --> 04:23.230
Shane: I DON'T KNOW.
WHY?

04:24.064 --> 04:26.967
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S PISSED AT ME.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.837
HE'S PISSED AT EVERYBODY.
IT'S IMPOTENT RAGE.

04:29.870 --> 04:31.805
FROM ME HOOKING UP
WITH PILAR.

04:31.839 --> 04:34.374
LET'S NOT TALK ABOUT THAT...
EVER AGAIN.

04:34.408 --> 04:35.576
DEAL?

04:35.609 --> 04:40.080
ANYWAY, I'M JUST...WORRIED SILAS
MIGHT DO SOMETHING STUPID.

04:40.113 --> 04:41.248
GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.016
YOU EVER BEEN
TO THE HAMPTONS?

04:43.050 --> 04:46.687
THE HAMPTONS? HUH.
I'VE BEEN TO THE BERKSHIRES,

04:46.720 --> 04:50.791
THE POCONOS, THE CATSKILLS ‐‐
LOVED THE CATSKILLS.

04:50.824 --> 04:52.793
WHEN I WAS A KID,
LENNY WOULD STOP THERE

04:52.826 --> 04:54.261
ON THE WAY
TO THE SARATOGA RACE TRACK

04:54.294 --> 04:57.264
TO HUSTLE GIN GAMES
OFF THE BALINSKY BROTHERS.

04:57.297 --> 04:59.933
HERBIE, HYMIE, AND HERSHEY ‐‐
MENSWEAR MAGNATES.

04:59.967 --> 05:01.068
OR WAS IT HANGERS?

05:01.101 --> 05:02.870
EITHER WAY, IT'S ‐‐
[ SNIFFS ]

05:02.903 --> 05:05.038
...TERRIBLE CARD PLAYERS.

05:05.072 --> 05:08.809
LOST MY VIRGINITY
AT GROSSINGER'S RESORT

05:08.842 --> 05:10.210
TO ALANA SPIEGEL.

05:10.244 --> 05:13.046
WE WERE PLAYING "CLUE."

05:13.080 --> 05:16.250
AND WHEN SHE SUGGESTED
IT WAS MRS. PEACOCK

05:16.283 --> 05:19.419
WITH THE LEAD PIPE
IN THE BALLROOM, WELL,

05:19.453 --> 05:22.189
I TOOK THE HINT
AND...BECAME A MAN.

05:22.222 --> 05:25.125
I WAS REALLY JUST LOOKING
FOR A "YES" OR A "NO."

05:25.158 --> 05:26.360
NO, NEVER BEEN.

05:26.393 --> 05:28.061
WELL, KLEIN LEFT
THIS AWESOME VACATION HOUSE

05:28.095 --> 05:29.329
IN EAST HAMPTON,

05:29.363 --> 05:31.131
AND WHIT AND I ARE GONNA THROW
THIS BIG, FANCY PARTY,

05:31.164 --> 05:34.001
TRY TO BRING IN SOME
HEAVY HITTERS INTO THE FUND.

05:34.034 --> 05:36.003
I NEED YOU TO PRETEND TO BE
AN INVESTOR

05:36.036 --> 05:37.971
WHO MADE A FORTUNE
OFF OF US.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.006
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

05:39.039 --> 05:40.207
LIKE BRINGING A HOT WOMAN
TO A BAR

05:40.240 --> 05:41.875
TO HELP PICK UP
OTHER HOT WOMEN.

05:41.909 --> 05:43.744
BE MY HOT WOMAN, ANDY.

05:43.777 --> 05:46.046
FLEECING NEW YORK'S UPPER CRUST
WHILE THEY'RE ON VACATION

05:46.079 --> 05:47.447
IS A BOTWIN FAMILY
TRADITION.

05:47.481 --> 05:49.316
I'M GOING WITH YOU.

05:49.349 --> 05:51.919
GREAT. YOU CAN PRETEND TO BE
MY TROPHY WIFE.

05:51.952 --> 05:54.421
NO TROPHY‐WIFE
PRETENDING.

05:54.454 --> 05:57.124
DRUG‐SELLING
TO PEOPLE WITH MONEY.

05:57.157 --> 05:59.359
I NEED
TO PAY DEMETRI BACK.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.261
COME ON, NANCE.
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

06:01.295 --> 06:03.964
THESE ARE WELL RESPECTED
MEMBERS OF HIGH SOCIETY.

06:03.997 --> 06:05.499
THEY DO COKE.

06:13.173 --> 06:17.177
[ SIGHS ]
HOW ARE YOU?

06:17.211 --> 06:19.746
OH.

06:19.780 --> 06:21.915
SEE? THOSE GUYS
LOOK LIKE HEBES.

06:21.949 --> 06:23.483
YOU'RE SAFE.

06:23.517 --> 06:26.820
GUYS, WE'RE IN LONG ISLAND,
NOT 1960s GEORGIA.

06:26.854 --> 06:28.622
[ SCOFFS ]

06:28.655 --> 06:29.890
FISHER!

06:29.923 --> 06:30.991
TILLERMAN!

06:31.024 --> 06:32.693
[ Chuckling ]
HEY.

06:32.726 --> 06:35.562
ROCKETMAN?
HOLY FUCKING CRAP.

06:35.596 --> 06:36.530
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN?

06:36.563 --> 06:39.099
THANKS FOR THE INVITE, FISH.
THIS IS NANCY.

06:39.132 --> 06:40.901
GIRLFRIEND? WIFE?

06:40.934 --> 06:41.969
MISTRESS.

06:42.002 --> 06:44.771
UH, NEITHER.
FRIEND. HI.

06:44.805 --> 06:46.306
FISHER ADAMS.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

06:46.340 --> 06:48.141
YOU CATCH UP
WITH YOUR LOST BOYS, HERE.

06:48.175 --> 06:49.643
I'M GONNA WANDER.

06:51.078 --> 06:53.881
FISH,
THIS IS BILL SUSSMAN.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.048
HE'S THE ONE
I WAS TELLING YOU

06:55.082 --> 06:56.316
BOUGHT KLEIN'S HOUSE
OVER BY GEORGICA POND.

06:56.350 --> 06:59.887
SORRY, BILL.
I‐I COULDN'T RESIST SPILLING IT.

06:59.920 --> 07:00.954
NOT A PROBLEM.

07:00.988 --> 07:02.289
YEAH, CLOSED ON IT
TWO DAYS AGO.

07:02.322 --> 07:04.925
WHY KEEP THE FRUITS
OF MY SUCCESS A SECRET?

07:04.958 --> 07:06.293
IF YOU CAN'T MAKE

07:06.326 --> 07:08.962
ALL YOUR FRIENDS OUTRAGEOUSLY
JEALOUS, WHAT'S THE POINT?

07:08.996 --> 07:10.430
ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

07:10.464 --> 07:11.865
BUT I DIDN'T KNOW KLEIN
WAS EVEN SELLING IT.

07:11.899 --> 07:13.333
I WOULD HAVE MADE A RUN AT IT
MYSELF.

07:13.367 --> 07:14.801
HE WASN'T.

07:14.835 --> 07:17.404
BILL MADE HIM AN OFFER
HE COULDN'T REFUSE.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.039
WELL, THANKS TO YOU GUYS
AND YOUR FUND,

07:19.072 --> 07:21.742
I COULD AFFORD
TO GROSSLY OVERPAY FOR IT,

07:21.775 --> 07:24.244
STILL HAVE ENOUGH LEFT OVER
FOR MY GIRLFRIEND'S ABORTION,

07:24.278 --> 07:26.079
A SMALL CASTLE
IN THE SOUTH OF FRANCE,

07:26.113 --> 07:28.682
AND, UH, PROSTHETIC BALLS
FOR MY DOG.

07:28.715 --> 07:31.518
YOU CAN DO THAT?
THEY'RE CALLED "NEUTICALS."
LOOK IT UP.

07:31.552 --> 07:32.886
HMM.

07:32.920 --> 07:34.321
WHERE'S KLEIN GOING?

07:34.354 --> 07:35.856
WELL, RUMOR HAS IT,
ONCE HE SEALS THE CHINA DEAL,

07:35.889 --> 07:37.257
HE'S GONNA MAKE A PLAY
FOR SPIELBERG'S HOUSE.

07:37.291 --> 07:39.393
HOW FUCKING PERFECT
IS THAT, HUH?

07:39.426 --> 07:42.062
A SHARK BUYING THE HOUSE
THAT "JAWS" BUILT.

07:42.095 --> 07:43.997
[ LAUGHS ]
I LOVE IT.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.332
OKAY, GUYS, TEE TIME.

07:45.365 --> 07:47.634
BILL,
ENJOY THE FACILITIES.

07:47.668 --> 07:50.904
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING ‐‐
AND I MEAN ANYTHING ‐‐

07:50.938 --> 07:52.806
I'M NUMBER 4‐5‐1
FOR THE CHITS.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.208
ALL RIGHT?

07:57.644 --> 07:58.612
HMM.

07:58.645 --> 08:01.148
OKAY,
ONE LONG ISLAND ICE TEA.
[ SIGHS ]

08:01.181 --> 08:03.350
SIGN THE CHIT, PLEASE.

08:03.383 --> 08:04.251
SHIT.

08:04.284 --> 08:07.955
5‐4‐1, 4‐5‐1?
IT'S MY SHORT‐TERM MEMORY.

08:07.988 --> 08:11.658
JUST PICK ONE.
NOBODY KNOWS THE DIFFERENCE.
OKAY.

08:13.026 --> 08:15.095
THANK YOU.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.498
MMM!

08:18.532 --> 08:19.967
NANCE ‐‐ CHITS.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.969
WE CAN SIGN
FOR WHATEVER WE WANT.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.804
I FEEL LIKE A STEAK ‐‐
THREE STEAKS.

08:23.837 --> 08:25.272
DO YOU THINK IT WOULD BE
TOO OBNOXIOUS

08:25.305 --> 08:27.941
TO BUY A DOZEN SWEATERS IN
THE PRO SHOP? IT PROBABLY WOULD.

08:27.975 --> 08:31.345
THE POOL LOOKS INVITING.
SHALL WE SWIM? OR TENNIS?

08:31.378 --> 08:33.347
OR TENNIS AND THEN SWIM?
We need to get to work.

08:33.380 --> 08:35.182
HMM? WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
WALK AROUND GOING...

08:35.215 --> 08:36.450
"Psst, drugs over here"?

08:36.483 --> 08:38.919
NO, WE NEED TO SCHMOOZE
TO GET PEOPLE TO COME

08:38.952 --> 08:41.555
TO THE PARTY TONIGHT,
AND THEN WE CAN SAY...

08:41.588 --> 08:43.357
"Psst, drugs over here."

08:43.390 --> 08:45.659
RIGHT, SCHMOOZE.
I'M GOOD AT THAT.

08:45.692 --> 08:47.961
YOU TAKE THE MAIN ROOM.
I'LL TAKE THE PATIO.

08:47.995 --> 08:50.731
LONG ISLAND ICE TEAS
ARE DELICIOUS.

08:50.764 --> 08:52.733
WHAT'S IN THEM?
MM. EVERYTHING.

08:52.766 --> 08:54.668
I MEAN REALLY DELICIOUS.

08:54.701 --> 08:55.969
ALL RIGHT.
LET ME TRY.

08:56.003 --> 08:57.471
THEY'RE FREE.
GET YOUR OWN.

09:00.774 --> 09:03.977
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

09:04.011 --> 09:05.913
THANKS, KID.

09:05.946 --> 09:07.581
WHERE'S MY CHANGE?

09:07.614 --> 09:08.982
OH.

09:11.485 --> 09:12.953
THAT'S IT?

09:12.986 --> 09:15.255
YOU THINK I'M HOLDING OUT
ON YOU?

09:15.289 --> 09:16.657
MOTHERFUCKING STARBUCKS.

09:16.690 --> 09:19.660
LISTEN, WE GETTING OUR COFFEE
AT MICKEY D's FROM NOW ON.

09:19.693 --> 09:21.228
YEAH,
YOU AND YOUR McDONALD'S.

09:21.261 --> 09:23.664
LISTEN, BETZ, THEY NEVER DID
YOUR ASS ANY FAVORS.

09:23.697 --> 09:26.066
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,
I WORKED THERE ONE SUMMER.

09:26.099 --> 09:27.868
GOT MORE PUSSY
THAN YOU WOULD BELIEVE.

09:27.901 --> 09:28.936
USED TO ASK THE LADIES

09:28.969 --> 09:30.571
IF THEY WANTED ME
TO SUPER‐SIZE IT.

09:30.604 --> 09:32.439
[ CHUCKLES ] YOU CAN ALWAYS
GO BACK, YOU KNOW.

09:32.472 --> 09:34.274
SO, I ORGANIZED
YOUR ARREST WARRANTS

09:34.308 --> 09:36.109
ALPHABETICALLY
AND BY COURT DATE

09:36.143 --> 09:37.811
SO YOU CAN ACCESS THEM
MORE EASILY.

09:37.845 --> 09:40.013
RADAR FUCKING O'REILLY.

09:40.047 --> 09:42.049
HEY,
TIME TO HIT THIS SHIT.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.387
OKAY, KID. COME ON.

09:47.421 --> 09:49.790
THROW THIS ON.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.459
SERIOUSLY?
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

09:52.492 --> 09:55.996
JUST SHUT UP
AND DO AS I SAY, OKAY?

09:56.029 --> 09:57.898
YOU'RE ABOUT TO FIND OUT

09:57.931 --> 10:00.868
HOW CLOSE YOU FLEW
TO THE FUCKING FLAME.

10:00.901 --> 10:03.070
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

10:05.072 --> 10:09.743
A 1969 DRC ROMANEE
CONTI ROUGE.

10:09.776 --> 10:11.211
SICK VINTAGE.

10:11.245 --> 10:14.014
MY GUY WHO IMPORTS IT,
ONLY $3,700 A BOTTLE FOR ME.

10:14.047 --> 10:15.048
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

10:15.082 --> 10:16.984
HE'S NOT TAKING
ANY NEW CUSTOMERS.

10:17.017 --> 10:19.653
FUCK YOU. NOW I REALLY
GOT TO KNOW HIS NAME.

10:19.686 --> 10:21.121
SORRY, PAL.
HE'S A MYSTERY.

10:21.154 --> 10:22.222
THE MAN HAS A NAME.

10:22.256 --> 10:24.625
NO CAN DO.
NO CAN DO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:24.658 --> 10:26.894
SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

10:26.927 --> 10:30.998
DID YOU JUST SAY
$3,700 A BOTTLE?

10:31.031 --> 10:32.432
YES, I DID.

10:32.466 --> 10:33.467
[ LAUGHS ]

10:33.500 --> 10:35.769
HOW MUCH BETTER IS THAT
THAN ONE THAT COSTS...

10:35.802 --> 10:38.772
I DON'T KNOW ‐‐
$300 A BOTTLE?

10:38.805 --> 10:40.874
$3,400 BETTER.

10:40.908 --> 10:43.810
I SEE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:43.844 --> 10:45.245
SORRY IF YOU WERE EXPECTING
SOME SOLILOQUY

10:45.279 --> 10:47.781
ON TANNINS AND BOUQUETS,
BUT THE TRUTH IS,

10:47.814 --> 10:49.816
I DRINK IT
'CAUSE I CAN AFFORD IT.

10:49.850 --> 10:52.819
FASCINATING.

10:52.853 --> 10:53.887
DOES THAT TURN YOU ON?

10:53.921 --> 10:55.355
YES, IT DOES.

10:55.389 --> 10:57.024
MEN WASTING
LARGE SUMS OF MONEY

10:57.057 --> 10:58.659
DEFINITELY TURNS ME
ALL THE WAY ON.

10:58.692 --> 11:01.028
SO MUCH SO THAT
I'D LIKE TO INVITE YOU BOTH

11:01.061 --> 11:03.197
TO A PARTY TONIGHT.

11:04.831 --> 11:07.167
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:08.836 --> 11:09.970
OH, HI.

11:10.003 --> 11:11.471
I'M SOPHIA.

11:11.505 --> 11:12.940
BILL SUSSMAN.

11:12.973 --> 11:18.245
SO, MY GIRLFRIENDS AND I,
WE HAVE A WAGER GOING.

11:18.278 --> 11:20.914
TRYING TO GUESS
WHAT YOU DO FOR A LIVING.

11:20.948 --> 11:22.616
I GOT MY LAW DEGREE
FROM DARTMOUTH

11:22.649 --> 11:24.251
BEFORE I JOINED
CREDIT SUISSE.

11:24.284 --> 11:28.088
THE HOURS KILLED ME,
SO I INVENTED AN iPhone APP

11:28.121 --> 11:30.691
THAT I SOLD TO RUSSIA
CALLED "WORDS WITH COMRADES."

11:30.724 --> 11:34.328
AND NOW I'M WRITING THE SCORE
FOR THE BROADWAY ADAPTATION

11:34.361 --> 11:37.931
OF, UH, THE MOST BELOVED
TELEVISION SHOW OF ALL TIME,

11:37.965 --> 11:39.099
"THE FACTS OF LIFE."

11:39.132 --> 11:41.268
HMM. YOU'RE FUNNY.

11:41.301 --> 11:43.904
HEY, LOOK, I'M HAVING
A HOUSEWARMING PARTY TONIGHT

11:43.937 --> 11:47.608
AT MY...NEW PROPERTY.

11:47.641 --> 11:50.277
WHY DON'T YOU
BRING YOUR FRIENDS?
COUNT US IN.

11:50.310 --> 11:51.778
I WILL.

11:51.812 --> 11:53.413
WANT TO GET ME A DRINK?

11:54.915 --> 11:56.850
LONG ISLAND ICE TEA,
MAKE IT A DOUBLE.

11:56.884 --> 11:58.719
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

11:58.752 --> 11:59.887
POUNCY HOUSE PARTY RENTALS.

11:59.920 --> 12:01.855
RIGHT THERE, SHITHEAD.
WHAT THE FUCK?

12:01.889 --> 12:06.226
NOW, THIS IS WHAT I CALL
A FUCKING PARTY.

12:06.260 --> 12:08.896
GOD DAMN IT. YOU PROMISED ME
THIS WOULD NEVER HAPPEN.

12:08.929 --> 12:10.063
SHUT THE FUCK UP,
DENNY.

12:10.097 --> 12:11.732
SEND THE KID IN.

12:11.765 --> 12:12.733
[ GROANS ]

12:12.766 --> 12:14.368
THESE CUFFS
ARE A LITTLE TIGHT.

12:14.401 --> 12:15.402
OH, I'M SORRY

12:15.435 --> 12:17.905
THEY'RE NOT MADE OUT OF SILVER,
YOUR HIGHNESS.

12:17.938 --> 12:19.473
HEY, MAYBE
WHEN YOU GET OUT

12:19.506 --> 12:21.642
FROM DOING 8 TO 12
FOR DISTRIBUTION,

12:21.675 --> 12:24.645
YOUR PARENTS MIGHT GET YOU
A PAIR FROM TIFFANY'S.

12:24.678 --> 12:26.380
HEY,
HERE'S THE THING, KID.

12:26.413 --> 12:27.548
UP TO THIS POINT,

12:27.581 --> 12:31.018
IT'S A LOT MORE FUN
STANDING ON THE OTHER SIDE.

12:31.051 --> 12:32.920
BUT WHEN THE HAMMER
COMES DOWN ‐‐

12:32.953 --> 12:34.021
AND IT ALWAYS COMES DOWN ‐‐

12:34.054 --> 12:35.522
YOU GOT TO BE
STANDING ON MY SIDE.

12:35.556 --> 12:38.192
WHAT IS THIS,
A FUCKING CIVICS CLASS?

12:38.225 --> 12:39.860
YEAH, AND YOU WISH YOU'D PAID
A LOT MORE FUCKING ATTENTION

12:39.893 --> 12:41.195
WHEN YOU WERE
IN THAT FUCKING CLASS.

12:41.228 --> 12:44.932
I WAS PHI BETA KAPPA,
YOU BLUE‐COLLAR PIECE OF SHIT.

12:44.965 --> 12:46.867
I WANT TO TALK
TO MY LAWYER.

12:46.900 --> 12:49.002
YOU SEE HOW "ANGELINA JOLIE"
SHE'S BEING?

12:49.036 --> 12:50.237
TRUST ME, BOTWIN,

12:50.270 --> 12:53.574
SHE'S SHITTING
HER DOLCE & GABBANAS RIGHT NOW.

12:53.607 --> 12:54.908
LET'S GET RID
OF THE PUTRID POT PRINCESS.

12:54.942 --> 12:56.844
COME ON, PARTNER.

12:56.877 --> 13:00.347
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

13:00.380 --> 13:03.483
SO, LISTEN,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY

13:03.517 --> 13:05.252
ABOUT ANYTHING ANYMORE.

13:05.285 --> 13:08.088
YOUR BROTHER HAS A CHANCE
TO WALK AWAY FROM THIS

13:08.121 --> 13:11.291
AND START CLEAN,
AND SO DO YOU.

13:11.325 --> 13:13.560
MY BROTHER?

13:14.962 --> 13:16.430
RIGHT.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.165
NOT HERE.

13:22.903 --> 13:24.571
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:28.342 --> 13:32.813
THERE'S AN OLD VET IN THERE
RANTING ABOUT THE WAR.

13:32.846 --> 13:34.681
PEOPLE ARE TOTALLY CAPTIVATED.
IT'S AMAZING.

13:34.715 --> 13:37.918
IF YOU TOOK THE SAME GUY,
TELLING THE SAME STORY,

13:37.951 --> 13:39.887
PUT HIM ON THE STREET CORNER
WITH A SHOPPING CART,

13:39.920 --> 13:41.622
HE'D BE
A BABBLING OLD FOOL.

13:41.655 --> 13:44.825
BUT BECAUSE HE HAS MONEY,
HE'S A WITTY RACONTEUR.

13:44.858 --> 13:45.993
UH‐HUH.

13:46.026 --> 13:50.430
THOSE TWO GUYS OVER THERE
PAID $3,700

13:50.464 --> 13:52.733
FOR A BOTTLE OF WINE
FROM FRANCE.

13:52.766 --> 13:55.068
WELL, FRANCE MAKES GOOD WINE.
I THINK IT'S THE SOIL...

13:55.102 --> 13:57.371
OR THE WATER.
OR THE ALCOHOL.

13:57.404 --> 13:59.206
NO, THEY'RE JUST
SHOWING OFF TO PROVE

13:59.239 --> 14:03.277
THEY'RE BIGGER,
RICHER, BETTER.

14:03.310 --> 14:07.247
AND...I'M GONNA DO THAT
WITH WEED.

14:07.281 --> 14:08.849
DO WHAT?

14:08.882 --> 14:10.684
PUT IT IN A FANCY BOX!

14:10.717 --> 14:12.619
Sell it for
a shit‐load of money.

14:12.653 --> 14:15.389
SAY IT'S FROM FRANCE,
TELL THEM THEY CAN'T HAVE IT.

14:15.422 --> 14:16.423
GOTCHA.

14:16.456 --> 14:19.259
LUXURY POT YOU CAN'T
GET YOUR HANDS ON, MM‐HMM.

14:19.293 --> 14:22.963
IN THE CORPORATE WORLD,
THAT'S CALLED RE‐BRANDING.

14:22.996 --> 14:25.566
I'M A TITAN NOW.
I KNOW ALL THE TERMS.

14:25.599 --> 14:29.903
UM, GROWN IN
THE LUSH HILLS OF PROVENCE,

14:29.937 --> 14:31.905
1,000 YEARS OF BLOOD
IN THE SOIL

14:31.939 --> 14:35.475
TO MAKE IT COMPLEX
AND WONDERFUL.

14:35.509 --> 14:36.910
YOU'RE GOOD AT THIS.

14:36.944 --> 14:39.246
NECTAR OF THE GODS.

14:39.279 --> 14:40.814
TOUGH GAME?

14:40.848 --> 14:42.616
[ GROANS ]
18 HOLES OF PURE TORTURE.

14:42.649 --> 14:44.618
HIT EVERY BUNKER
AND HAD TO LISTEN TO FISHER

14:44.651 --> 14:46.787
BRAG ABOUT HIS FOURTH WIFE
WHO USED TO BE A STRIPPER

14:46.820 --> 14:49.523
AND CAN ONLY GET OFF WHEN SHE
TAKES IT UP THE "TUCHUS."

14:49.556 --> 14:51.158
I'M GONNA GO IN TO TOWN.

14:51.191 --> 14:54.761
I'M GONNA GET SOME FANCY BOXES,
SOME RIBBON.

14:54.795 --> 14:57.431
<i>UNE MéRE</i>
<i>QUE J'AIMERIAS BAISER.</i>

14:57.464 --> 14:58.866
WHAT'S THAT?

14:58.899 --> 15:00.067
IT'S FRENCH FOR MILF.

15:00.100 --> 15:02.302
I'M GONNA TAKE THE LIMO.
YOU GUYS GET A TAXI.

15:04.505 --> 15:05.973
[ SIGHS ]

15:06.006 --> 15:07.441
WHAT'S WRONG?

15:07.474 --> 15:09.476
THAT'S MY LIMO.

15:13.113 --> 15:14.948
GUESS WHAT I JUST DID.

15:14.982 --> 15:17.417
IN ORDER TO DO THAT,
I'D HAVE TO GIVE A SHIT.

15:17.451 --> 15:19.253
OH, I THINK
YOU'LL GIVE A SHIT.

15:19.286 --> 15:20.888
GET OUT OF HERE, SHANE.

15:20.921 --> 15:23.156
I WATCHED A DRUG BUST.

15:24.124 --> 15:26.026
POUNCY HOUSE
WENT DOWN TODAY.

15:26.059 --> 15:27.995
IT WAS PRETTY AWESOME.

15:28.028 --> 15:29.463
IT WAS LIKE
A "LAW & ORDER" EPISODE

15:29.496 --> 15:30.330
EXCEPT FOR ALL THE COPS

15:30.364 --> 15:31.899
DIDN'T LOOK
LIKE UNEMPLOYED ACTORS.

15:31.932 --> 15:32.933
EMMA?

15:32.966 --> 15:34.334
NICE JOB TAPPING THAT.

15:34.368 --> 15:36.904
SHE'S A LOT CUTER IN PERSON
THAN ON HER SURVEILLANCE PHOTO.

15:36.937 --> 15:38.906
YOU SAW HER GET BUSTED?

15:38.939 --> 15:40.641
YEAH, OUELLETTE
LET ME COME ALONG.

15:40.674 --> 15:44.244
GOT TO HAND IT TO MOM.
ALL HER ENEMIES ‐‐ VANQUISHED.

15:45.212 --> 15:48.015
WHAT THE HELL DID MOM
HAVE TO DO WITH IT?

15:48.048 --> 15:49.283
SHE TOLD OUELLETTE

15:49.316 --> 15:52.486
THAT MY BIG BROTHER
WAS INVOLVED WITH POUNCY HOUSE

15:52.519 --> 15:53.954
AND I LOOKED UP TO YOU.

15:53.987 --> 15:56.557
SO, IN ORDER TO SAVE ME,
HE HAD TO BUST THEM.

15:56.590 --> 15:59.126
PRETTY FUCKING GENIUS.
HAVE YOU HEARD FROM HER?

15:59.159 --> 16:02.029
I DON'T KNOW IF SHE WAS
SUPPOSED TO COME BACK TONIGHT.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.664
[ SIGHS ]

16:03.697 --> 16:05.966
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:05.999 --> 16:08.435
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

16:08.468 --> 16:10.103
THAT'S OUR DATABASE.

16:10.137 --> 16:12.272
YOU AND MOM
CAN GO FUCK YOURSELVES!

16:18.245 --> 16:21.381
[ SEA GULLS SQUAWKING ]

16:21.415 --> 16:23.684
THIS PRODUCT IS
FROM THE SOUTH, PROVENCE.

16:23.717 --> 16:27.754
THE WATER IS FILTERED THROUGH
MEDITERRANEAN LIMESTONE.

16:27.788 --> 16:29.756
MAKES A BIG DIFFERENCE
IN THE <i>TERROIR.</i>

16:29.790 --> 16:31.592
IT'S MORE EXPENSIVE,
OBVIOUSLY.

16:31.625 --> 16:32.726
BUT REMEMBER ‐‐

16:32.759 --> 16:37.965
ONE PUFF IS EQUAL TO FOUR,
FIVE OF A REGULAR STRAIN.

16:37.998 --> 16:39.199
I HAVE PREMIUM,

16:39.233 --> 16:41.602
SOMETHING I OFFER
TO PREFERRED CUSTOMERS ONLY.

16:41.635 --> 16:43.971
SUPPLY IS LIMITED.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.607
I'LL TAKE TWO BOXES.

16:46.640 --> 16:48.709
BEEN AROUND SINCE
LOUIS XIV.

16:48.742 --> 16:52.045
SUPPOSEDLY, HIS SERVANTS GREW
AN IMPORTED BELGIAN STRAIN

16:52.079 --> 16:55.883
NEAR THE, UM, THE GARDENS,
UH, AT VERSAILLES.

16:55.916 --> 16:58.752
IT'S MORE AROMATIC
THAN AMERICAN WEED,

16:58.785 --> 17:00.988
MORE, UM, ARTISANAL.

17:01.021 --> 17:02.222
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:02.256 --> 17:03.957
YEAH, HIS FIRST TWO WIVES
NEVER LET HIM SMOKE.

17:03.991 --> 17:05.526
THEY'RE OLD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:05.559 --> 17:07.661
I LOVE GETTING HIGH
AND SUCKING HIS COCK.

17:07.694 --> 17:08.662
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:08.695 --> 17:09.863
OH.

17:09.897 --> 17:11.665
WE'LL TAKE FIVE BOXES.

17:11.698 --> 17:12.866
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

17:12.900 --> 17:14.835
OH, IT'S ONLY TWO
PER CUSTOMER.

17:14.868 --> 17:16.270
I'LL PAY DOUBLE.

17:16.303 --> 17:19.039
WELL, I ‐‐ I'M REALLY
NOT SUPPOSED TO DO THIS,

17:19.072 --> 17:22.142
BUT, UM, YOUR STORY'S
REALLY TOUCHED MY HEART,

17:22.176 --> 17:24.978
SO CONSIDER IT
A BELATED WEDDING GIFT.

17:25.012 --> 17:28.048
ALL I WANT TO KNOW,
WILL IT TAKE THE EDGE OFF?

17:28.081 --> 17:29.516
DEFINITELY.
I'LL TAKE IT.

17:29.550 --> 17:31.552
I'M CRAZED WITH GETTING
MY TWINS INTO PRESCHOOL.

17:31.585 --> 17:35.355
WELL, IF YOU START THEM EARLY
WITH A GOOD EDUCATION ‐‐

17:35.389 --> 17:37.858
60 GRAND TO FINGER‐PAINT
AND PILE BLOCKS.

17:37.891 --> 17:39.826
IF WE CAN EVEN GET IN.

17:39.860 --> 17:41.495
WE SAT DOWN
WITH OUR ACCOUNTANT LAST WEEK

17:41.528 --> 17:43.297
AND REALIZED
IT'S GONNA COST OVER $1 MILLION

17:43.330 --> 17:45.232
TO EDUCATE
THOSE TWO LITTLE ANIMALS.

17:45.265 --> 17:46.900
AND THAT'S
NOT COUNTING COLLEGE

17:46.934 --> 17:48.202
PLUS
ALL THE GIFTS AND BRIBES.

17:48.235 --> 17:50.737
I BOUGHT A BOOK ON CUNNILINGUS
IN CASE I HAVE TO GO DOWN

17:50.771 --> 17:52.739
ON THIS ONE
DYKE ADMISSIONS NAZI.

17:52.773 --> 17:53.974
YOU HAVE LITTLE ONES?

17:54.007 --> 17:55.042
I HAVE A 4‐YEAR‐OLD.

17:55.075 --> 17:56.410
WELL, I HOPE YOU SELL
A LOT OF DRUGS

17:56.443 --> 17:57.311
'CAUSE YOU'LL NEED IT.

17:57.344 --> 17:59.012
THAT AND A QUICK TONGUE,
I GUESS.

17:59.046 --> 18:00.881
YOU SAID $500?

18:00.914 --> 18:01.882
YES.

18:01.915 --> 18:03.350
I'LL TAKE 20.

18:08.622 --> 18:10.557
HOW GOES THE FISHING?

18:10.591 --> 18:12.759
TURNS OUT KLEIN ALREADY PULLED
HALF THE PEOPLE HERE

18:12.793 --> 18:13.861
INTO THE FUND.

18:13.894 --> 18:15.162
AND THE OTHER HALF
GOT TAKEN BY MADOFF,

18:15.195 --> 18:17.164
SO NOBODY WANTS TO
GO NEAR A HEDGE FUND

18:17.197 --> 18:19.166
UNLESS THEY KNOW FOR SURE
THEY'RE ON THE TOP RUNG.

18:19.199 --> 18:22.336
I MEAN, THIS PARTY
IS ONE COLOSSAL DRY HUMP.

18:22.369 --> 18:24.505
WE'RE SCREWED.

18:26.740 --> 18:28.008
I CAN SAVE YOU.

18:28.041 --> 18:29.710
YOU FIND SOMEONE?

18:29.743 --> 18:31.478
ATTAGIRL. WHO?

18:31.512 --> 18:32.946
FIRST, A DEAL.

18:32.980 --> 18:34.281
WHAT KIND OF DEAL?

18:34.314 --> 18:39.419
I HAVE BEEN SELLING DIME BAGS
ALL NIGHT FOR $500 A POP

18:39.453 --> 18:41.722
JUST BY TELLING PEOPLE
THEY'RE FROM FRANCE,

18:41.755 --> 18:44.358
PUTTING A PRETTY BOW ON IT.

18:44.391 --> 18:46.894
YOU GUYS FUND ME,
I COULD EXPAND,

18:46.927 --> 18:50.030
BECOME THE GREY GOOSE
OF WEED.

18:50.063 --> 18:52.032
WE'RE ALREADY
BREAKING THE LAW.

18:52.065 --> 18:53.066
[ SIGHS ]

18:53.100 --> 18:55.736
WE NEED MONEY <i>IN,</i>
NOT <i>OUT.</i>

18:55.769 --> 18:57.237
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

18:57.271 --> 18:58.972
DO YOU SEE THAT GUY
OVER THERE?

18:59.006 --> 19:00.974
IN THE YELLOW SHIRT?
BY THE BAR?

19:01.008 --> 19:03.310
WORTH A FORTUNE.

19:03.343 --> 19:04.344
COAL MINES.

19:04.378 --> 19:06.980
DRINKS $3,700
BOTTLES OF WINE.

19:07.014 --> 19:08.215
HE'S LOOKING FOR A PLACE
TO PARK HIS CASH

19:08.248 --> 19:11.251
SO THAT HIS EX‐WIFE
CAN'T GET HER HANDS ON IT.

19:11.285 --> 19:14.288
YOU HELP ME,
COAL MINER'S ALL YOURS.

19:14.321 --> 19:17.524
ALL RIGHT, STOP BY
THE OFFICE NEXT WEEK
WITH A BUSINESS PLAN.

19:17.558 --> 19:18.959
WE'LL TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

19:18.992 --> 19:20.827
NOW, COME ON,
INTRODUCE US TO THE GUY.

19:20.861 --> 19:22.963
HANG ON.

19:22.996 --> 19:24.431
UH, ANDY, COME ON.

19:24.464 --> 19:25.966
I NEED YOU
TO COME VOUCH FOR THE FIRM.

19:25.999 --> 19:29.002
CAN'T. THERE'S A HOT
REDHEAD AT THE BAR IN A
FALLOPIAN‐LENGTH DRESS

19:29.036 --> 19:31.138
THAT I DEFINITELY
WANT A PIECE OF.

19:31.171 --> 19:33.307
OKAY, BUKOWSKI,
I'M CUTTING YOU OFF.

19:33.340 --> 19:34.141
WHAT?!

19:34.174 --> 19:38.145
NO! NOBODY CUTS
BILL SUSSMAN OFF!

19:38.178 --> 19:39.847
I DON'T THINK
I'VE EVER SEEN YOU THIS DRUNK.

19:39.880 --> 19:40.814
BILL SUSSMAN
DOESN'T GET DRUNK.

19:40.848 --> 19:42.816
BILL SUSSMAN CAN HOLD
HIS BOOZE.

19:42.850 --> 19:45.619
CAN BILL SUSSMAN
COME HELP ME NOW?

19:45.652 --> 19:47.821
NO, BILL SUSSMAN
CANNOT COME HELP YOU NOW.

19:47.855 --> 19:48.956
KNOW WHY?

19:48.989 --> 19:50.324
BILL SUSSMAN DOESN'T FOLLOW
CHICKS AROUND

19:50.357 --> 19:52.192
EVERY TIME
THEY SNAP THEIR FINGERS

19:52.226 --> 19:53.727
LIKE A PATHETIC
CHICK‐FOLLOWER.

19:53.760 --> 19:56.797
BILL SUSSMAN DOES WHAT HE WANTS
WHENEVER HE WANTS IT.

19:56.830 --> 19:58.265
DO THAT AGAIN,
YOU'RE A DEAD MAN.

19:58.298 --> 19:59.933
COME ON.
ADMIT IT. YOU WANT IT.

19:59.967 --> 20:01.535
BILL SUSSMAN TURNS YOU ON,
RIGHT?

20:01.568 --> 20:03.904
OKAY, OKAY, IF YOU JUST HELP ME
NOW FOR FIVE MINUTES,

20:03.937 --> 20:05.939
THEN I'LL GO GET YOU
UP INTO BED, OKAY?

20:05.973 --> 20:07.708
BED? BED?!

20:07.741 --> 20:09.109
BILL SUSSMAN
DOESN'T DO IT IN BED.

20:09.142 --> 20:11.945
HE DOES IT ON A BEAR‐SKIN RUG,
BARE BACK, AND BACKWARDS.

20:11.979 --> 20:12.946
[ SIGHS ]

20:12.980 --> 20:14.348
YOU'RE GONNA BEND
FOR ME, BITCH.

20:14.381 --> 20:15.983
EXCUSE ME.
WHAT'S UP? I'M SORRY.

20:16.016 --> 20:18.218
WILL YOU PLEASE,
PLEASE STOP ACTING LIKE THIS?!

20:18.252 --> 20:19.953
I REALLY NEED
YOUR HELP RIGHT NOW!

20:19.987 --> 20:23.490
I HAVE A LOT TO LEARN
FROM SOMEONE LIKE BILL.

20:23.524 --> 20:26.827
DOING IT HIS WAY, REFUSING
TO TAKE NO FOR AN ANSWER,

20:26.860 --> 20:29.363
'CAUSE THAT'S
HOW HE GOT HIS FORTUNE.

20:29.396 --> 20:32.666
THERE IS NO FORTUNE.
BILL SUSSMAN DOESN'T EXIST.

20:32.699 --> 20:33.901
WELL, HE SHOULD.

20:33.934 --> 20:37.271
ANDY BOTWIN...
SLEEPS ON AN AIR MATTRESS,

20:37.304 --> 20:41.808
HAS TO BORROW MONEY FROM A KID
TO START A BUSINESS

20:41.842 --> 20:43.076
THAT'S ABOUT TO GO
BELLY‐UP,

20:43.110 --> 20:46.980
AND IS OBSESSED WITH A WOMAN
WHO'S A SELF‐CENTERED,

20:47.014 --> 20:48.682
HEARTLESS SOCIOPATH.

20:48.715 --> 20:50.284
IF YOU MEAN ME, FUCK YOU.

20:50.317 --> 20:52.853
THE TRUTH HURTS,
DOESN'T IT?

20:52.886 --> 20:54.321
TRUTH IS
BILL SUSSMAN'S A DICK.

20:54.354 --> 20:57.691
HEY, CHOP‐CHOP.
THE COAL MINER'S ABOUT TO LEAVE.

20:57.724 --> 20:58.926
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HIM?

20:58.959 --> 21:03.096
[ SIGHS ] TOO MANY
LONG ISLAND ICE TEAS.
Fuck.

21:04.598 --> 21:05.966
Hey.

21:05.999 --> 21:10.237
I KNOW THAT IN ‐‐
I‐I KNOW THAT IN THE PAST,

21:10.270 --> 21:12.906
BILL SUSSMAN AND I
HAVE HAD OUR DIFFERENCES.

21:12.940 --> 21:15.943
BUT I REALLY DON'T THINK
I CAN DO IT

21:15.976 --> 21:17.778
WITHOUT HIS HELP
RIGHT NOW.

21:17.811 --> 21:19.079
OH, YEAH?

21:19.112 --> 21:22.649
OH. WELL, NOW YOU SEE THE POWER
OF BILL SUSSMAN, HUH?

21:22.683 --> 21:23.884
[ IMITATES HONKING ]

21:23.917 --> 21:24.852
BLECH! FINE.

21:24.885 --> 21:27.187
BUT I'M DOING IT FOR DOUG!
YEAH.

21:27.221 --> 21:29.122
BILL SUSSMAN DOES THINGS
FOR HIS BUDDIES.

21:29.156 --> 21:30.157
OKAY, WHICH ONE IS HE?

21:30.190 --> 21:31.725
THE GUY
IN THE YELLOW SHIRT.

21:32.860 --> 21:34.962
OH!
WATCH IT, BUDDY.

21:34.995 --> 21:36.597
SHIT.
IS HE TOO WASTED?

21:36.630 --> 21:38.999
PROBABLY, BUT THAT'S OKAY.
JANSEN IS, TOO.

21:42.569 --> 21:43.704
OHH.

21:43.737 --> 21:46.673
SEE? ALL GOOD.

21:49.176 --> 21:51.612
[ GROANS ]
PAIN.

21:51.645 --> 21:53.247
I'M TELLING YOU.

21:53.280 --> 21:54.915
A RAW EGG MIXED
WITH A LITTLE CLAMATO

21:54.948 --> 21:56.083
AND SOME
CRUSHED‐UP OREOS...

21:56.116 --> 21:57.618
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
...WORKS LIKE A CHARM.

21:57.651 --> 21:58.919
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

21:58.952 --> 22:01.522
IF YOU SAY THE WORD "CLAMATO"
ONE MORE TIME,

22:01.555 --> 22:02.689
I'M GONNA HEAVE AGAIN.

22:02.723 --> 22:05.058
HEY, YOU LOOKED SHARP IN KLEIN'S
CLOTHES. YOU SWIPE ANY?

22:05.092 --> 22:08.929
NO. WEIGHED ME DOWN.

22:08.962 --> 22:10.764
I'M MUCH HAPPIER
BEING ANDY BOTWIN.

22:10.797 --> 22:12.032
CAREFREE SOUL,

22:12.065 --> 22:16.270
TASTING ALL THE LOW‐HANGING
FRUIT LIFE HAS TO OFFER,

22:16.303 --> 22:18.272
A LOT LESS COMPLICATED,
A LOT MORE FUN.

22:18.305 --> 22:21.642
LET THE MASTERS OF THE UNIVERSE
DEAL WITH ALL THE CLIMBERS

22:21.675 --> 22:23.110
AND THEIR AGENDAS,
YOU KNOW?

22:23.143 --> 22:26.413
WITH ME, WHAT YOU SEE
IS WHAT YOU GET.

22:26.446 --> 22:29.116
AGAIN, I WAS REALLY JUST LOOKING
FOR A "YES" OR A "NO."

22:30.551 --> 22:32.986
SILAS.

22:33.020 --> 22:34.788
IT WAS A GREAT TRIP.

22:34.821 --> 22:37.090
MUCH TO DISCUSS.

22:37.124 --> 22:40.460
UH, BEFORE YOU COME AT ME
WITH BOTH BARRELS,

22:40.494 --> 22:41.962
LET ME JUST SAY,

22:41.995 --> 22:44.464
I HAVE BEEN THINKING ABOUT IT,
AND YOU WERE RIGHT.

22:44.498 --> 22:45.566
I WAS WRONG.

22:45.599 --> 22:49.903
I SHOULDN'T HAVE BIG‐FOOTED YOU
LIKE THAT WITH EMMA.

22:49.937 --> 22:51.538
I HAD MY REASONS,

22:51.572 --> 22:55.342
BUT YOU DESERVE MORE RESPECT
THAN THAT.

22:55.375 --> 22:56.977
[ SIGHS ]

22:57.010 --> 22:59.913
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN,

22:59.947 --> 23:02.916
AND I'LL LET YOU MAKE
MORE DECISIONS...

23:02.950 --> 23:04.685
IN THE FUTURE, OKAY?

23:04.718 --> 23:05.752
TRUCE?

23:05.786 --> 23:07.054
YOU HAD EMMA ARRESTED.

23:07.087 --> 23:10.023
EMMA HAD EMMA ARRESTED.
WITH YOUR HELP.

23:10.057 --> 23:11.058
POSSIBLY.

23:11.091 --> 23:12.559
THAT'S BULLSHIT.

23:12.593 --> 23:13.827
IT'S BUSINESS.

23:13.861 --> 23:15.329
AND YOU WEREN'T
EVEN GONNA TELL ME.

23:15.362 --> 23:16.864
YOU WOULD HAVE
JUST TOLD HER.

23:16.897 --> 23:18.899
WELL,
YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

23:18.932 --> 23:20.834
WHOSE SIDE ARE YOU ON?

23:20.868 --> 23:24.271
FROM NOW ON, MY OWN.

23:24.304 --> 23:26.473
HE DOWNLOADED
OUR DATABASE.

23:26.507 --> 23:27.808
FUCKING RAT.

23:27.841 --> 23:30.043
I PREFER THE TERM
"INFORMANT."

23:30.077 --> 23:32.813
WELL, THAT WASN'T
YOURS TO TAKE.

23:32.846 --> 23:36.250
WELL, GO AHEAD.
COME ON.

23:36.283 --> 23:37.551
TRY ME.

23:39.086 --> 23:43.524
I'M NOT GONNA FIGHT YOU
FOR IT, SILAS.

23:43.557 --> 23:46.827
PROBABLY A GOOD IDEA.

23:46.860 --> 23:49.863
CONSIDER ME...
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:49.897 --> 23:51.965
...THE COMPETITION.

23:51.999 --> 23:54.168
FAIR WARNING ‐‐

23:54.201 --> 23:58.005
EVERYTHING
IS UP FOR GRABS.

24:00.040 --> 24:03.243
AND BEST OF LUCK TO YOU,
NANCY.

24:07.381 --> 24:09.183
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
FUCK HIM.

24:09.216 --> 24:11.752
LET HIM GO.
WE DON'T NEED HIM.

24:17.824 --> 24:24.464
♪♪ IT WAS ALL BECAUSE
OF SOME UNFORTUNATE SEA ♪♪

24:24.498 --> 24:30.737
♪♪ YOU COULDN'T SWIM UNDER
WHAT CAME TO BE ♪♪

24:30.771 --> 24:36.443
♪♪ YOU HAD TO CHOOSE
TO GIVE IN TO THE WAVE ♪♪

24:36.476 --> 24:43.951
♪♪ LET THE FORCE OF ALL THINGS
TAKE YOU FAR AWAY ♪♪

24:43.984 --> 24:44.218
♪♪ OH‐OH, OH‐OH‐OH ♪♪
